{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JyH3J2xxLBFLptFFH6qoYk","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Stage 2 manual verification: parse real PLAN.md files in compat mode.\n2\t\n3\tRun as ``python -m bob_tools.planfile.tests.manual.check_compat_read``.\n4\t\n5\tFor each hard-coded path the script parses the file with\n6\t:func:`bob_tools.planfile.parse_plan` and prints exactly one line:\n7\t\n8\t    OK   <path> phases=<n> bugs=<true|false> bug_count=<n>\n9\t\n10\tWhen parsing raises, the line begins with ``FAIL`` and carries the\n11\texception class plus its message:\n12\t\n13\t    FAIL <path> <ExceptionClass>: <message>\n14\t\n15\tThe script exits non-zero if any path failed to parse, otherwise zero.\n16\t\n17\tThis replaces the long ``python -c \"...\"`` one-liner that task 2.8\n18\toriginally used; that form produced ``bugs=False`` for files without a\n19\tBugs section, which read as \"the bugs section is empty\" rather than\n20\t\"no Bugs section is present\" and confused the verification step. The\n21\t``bug_count`` field disambiguates: ``bugs=false bug_count=0`` is a\n22\tfile with no Bugs section, while ``bugs=true bug_count=0`` would be a\n23\tpresent-but-empty Bugs section, and ``bugs=true bug_count=N`` is the\n24\tnormal populated case.\n25\t\"\"\"\n26\t\n27\tfrom __future__ import annotations\n28\t\n29\timport sys\n30\tfrom pathlib import Path\n31\t\n32\tfrom bob_tools.planfile import bug_count, parse_plan\n33\t\n34\tPATHS: tuple[str, ...] = (\n35\t    \"/Users/mhcoen/proj/duplo/PLAN.md\",\n36\t    \"/Users/mhcoen/proj/mcloop/PLAN.md\",\n37\t    \"/Users/mhcoen/proj/mcloop/PLAN.EXAMPLE.md\",\n38\t)\n39\t\n40\t\n41\tdef main() -> int:\n42\t    failures = 0\n43\t    for path_str in PATHS:\n44\t        path = Path(path_str)\n45\t        try:\n46\t            text = path.read_text()\n47\t            plan = parse_plan(text)\n48\t        except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001\n49\t            failures += 1\n50\t            print(f\"FAIL {path_str} {type(exc).__name__}: {exc}\")\n51\t            continue\n52\t        phases = len(plan.phases)\n53\t        bugs_present = \"true\" if plan.bugs is not None else \"false\"\n54\t        bugs_n = bug_count(plan)\n55\t        print(f\"OK   {path_str} phases={phases} bugs={bugs_present} bug_count={bugs_n}\")\n56\t    return 1 if failures else 0\n57\t\n58\t\n59\tif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n60\t    sys.exit(main())\n61\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c61f1cb6-aab2-436d-a134-c2d01c95bc3d","uuid":"4181ebc2-1c3e-4733-ba4a-4aec448a6094","timestamp":"2026-05-16T13:49:09.735Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/mhcoen/proj/bob-tools/bob_tools/planfile/tests/manual/check_compat_read.py","content":"\"\"\"Stage 2 manual verification: parse real PLAN.md files in compat mode.\n\nRun as ``python -m bob_tools.planfile.tests.manual.check_compat_read``.\n\nFor each hard-coded path the script parses the file with\n:func:`bob_tools.planfile.parse_plan` and prints exactly one line:\n\n    OK   <path> phases=<n> bugs=<true|false> bug_count=<n>\n\nWhen parsing raises, the line begins with ``FAIL`` and carries the\nexception class plus its message:\n\n    FAIL <path> <ExceptionClass>: <message>\n\nThe script exits non-zero if any path failed to parse, otherwise zero.\n\nThis replaces the long ``python -c \"...\"`` one-liner that task 2.8\noriginally used; that form produced ``bugs=False`` for files without a\nBugs section, which read as \"the bugs section is empty\" rather than\n\"no Bugs section is present\" and confused the verification step. The\n``bug_count`` field disambiguates: ``bugs=false bug_count=0`` is a\nfile with no Bugs section, while ``bugs=true bug_count=0`` would be a\npresent-but-empty Bugs section, and ``bugs=true bug_count=N`` is the\nnormal populated case.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nfrom bob_tools.planfile import bug_count, parse_plan\n\nPATHS: tuple[str, ...] = (\n    \"/Users/mhcoen/proj/duplo/PLAN.md\",\n    \"/Users/mhcoen/proj/mcloop/PLAN.md\",\n    \"/Users/mhcoen/proj/mcloop/PLAN.EXAMPLE.md\",\n)\n\n\ndef main() -> int:\n    failures = 0\n    for path_str in PATHS:\n        path = Path(path_str)\n        try:\n            text = path.read_text()\n            plan = parse_plan(text)\n        except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001\n            failures += 1\n            print(f\"FAIL {path_str} {type(exc).__name__}: {exc}\")\n            continue\n        phases = len(plan.phases)\n        bugs_present = \"true\" if plan.bugs is not None else \"false\"\n        bugs_n = bug_count(plan)\n        print(f\"OK   {path_str} phases={phases} bugs={bugs_present} bug_count={bugs_n}\")\n    return 1 if failures else 0\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    sys.exit(main())\n","numLines":61,"startLine":1,"totalLines":61}}}
